00:14:10.989 --> 00:14:13.280
DENNIS FREEMAN: If it were
responding to the unit step,

00:14:13.280 --> 00:14:14.850
that's absolutely true.

00:14:14.850 --> 00:14:18.640
So if I'm thinking about
the unit-sample response,

00:14:18.640 --> 00:14:22.920
then the unit-sample response
always looks like p-naught

00:14:22.920 --> 00:14:26.740
to the n, n bigger
than or equal to 0.

00:14:30.030 --> 00:14:34.290
And there's no way you
can choose a p-naught that

00:14:34.290 --> 00:14:37.030
